    <briefdescription>
<para>API for appending new files in a table while merging manifests. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This API accumulates file additions, produces a new <ref refid="structiceberg_1_1Snapshot" kindref="compound">Snapshot</ref> of the table, and commits that snapshot as current. When committing, these changes are applied to the latest table snapshot. Commit conflicts are resolved by applying the changes to the new latest snapshot and reattempting the commit.</para>
<para><ref refid="classiceberg_1_1MergeAppend" kindref="compound">MergeAppend</ref> uses the shared <ref refid="classiceberg_1_1MergingSnapshotUpdate" kindref="compound">MergingSnapshotUpdate</ref> pipeline, so it can merge newly written and existing manifests according to table properties. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
